# Admin Testing Standards — YOM Admin Portal

Standards for testing the YOM Admin portal (`admin.youorder.me`).

## What is Admin

The Admin portal is used by **CLIENT_ADMIN** and **ADMIN** roles to manage the YOM platform for their client:

- Product management (catalog, pricing, promotions)
- Commerce management (invite, activate, block businesses)
- Order management (view, update status)
- Banner and branding configuration
- Store settings (payment methods, delivery dates, domain rules)
- User management (admin users, permissions)
- Reports and analytics

**Key difference from B2B:** Admin users manage the platform configuration. B2B users (comercios) buy products. Testing Admin means testing the configuration surface that affects all B2B users.

## Coverage Model

### What Cowork Tests

- Visual correctness of Admin pages
- Banner preview (does it look right for a given client?)
- Configuration flows that are hard to automate (e.g., image uploads, complex form interactions)
- First-time setup flows for new client onboarding
- Configuration that requires judgment (does this logo look right?)

### What Playwright Tests

- Authentication and authorization (role-based access control)
- CRUD operations (products, promotions, banners, commerces)
- Configuration flags that affect B2B (e.g., anonymous access, Khipu payments)
- Order status management
- Regression for Admin-driven incidents

### What Checklists Test

- Permissions matrix (which roles can do what)
- Order management edge cases (bulk updates, status transitions)
- Integration configuration (ERP hooks, webhooks setup)
- Report generation and data export

